  "texts": [
    "Why would one coin created out of code be valued in thousands of pounds and another coin created out of code be worth zero.",
    "It is often compared with traditional securities such as stock shares, but stocks generate cash flow, and we can discount the cash flow to the present time to come up with a valuation.",
    "Another example is that a fiat currency is valued relative to other fiat currencies based on GDP, inflation, interest rates, and other data from different countries.",
    "None of these valuations apply to cryptocurrencies.",
    "This means that cryptocurrencies cannot be valued because they do not have any trade fundamentals."
  ],
